<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4">The real story of the Clintons:</font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>The art of politics without conscience</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">February 23, 2007 | Pages 8 amd 9</font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">JEFFREY ST. CLAIR is coeditor of the muckraking Web site and newsletter <i><a href="http://www.counterpunch.org" target="_blank">CounterPunch</a>. </i>He is the author of numerous books, most recently <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEnd-Times-Fourth-Estate-Counterpunch%2Fdp%2F1904859372%2Fsr%3D8-10%2Fqid%3D1171853924%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">End Times: The Death of the Fourth Estate</a>, </i>a collection of essays about the media written with Alexander Cockburn that will appear in March.<p>
Here, he talks to <i>Socialist Worker's </i>ALAN MAASS about the story of the Bill Clinton presidency--and the long and grim record of the early frontrunner for the Democratic presidential nomination, Sen. Hillary Rodham Clinton.<p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</font></p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3"><b>WITH THE Bush presidency being such a disaster in every way, a lot of people now seem to look back at the Clinton years with nostalgia. Do the Clintons deserve this?</b><p>

I GUESS it depends on what side of those years you were on. If you made a lot of money in the stock market in those days, you might look back on it with nostalgia. For the rest of us, I think you only look back if you're forced to--at the scene of eight years of crime.<p>
The Clinton administration opened the doors for Bush Junior in ways that Junior's father never did. Aside from the obvious Oedipal things going on with Bush Junior, his father hasn't been a big help to him. But Clinton certainly has. When Bush talks about his "other father," people are assuming that he's talking to the supreme deity. But I think that maybe it's Clinton who's on the speed dial.<p>

<table width="270" align="right"><tr><td>
<table width="258" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" align="right" border="2" hspace="8" bordercolor="006699" bgcolor="#FFCC66"><tr><td>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Be sure to read the <i><a href="http://www.counterpunch.org" target="_blank">CounterPunch</a> </i>Web site, edited by Jeffrey St. Clair and Alexander Cockburn, for all the dirt on the presidential contenders as the 2008 campaign drags on and on.<p>
Cockburn and St. Clair's latest book is <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEnd-Times-Fourth-Estate-Counterpunch%2Fdp%2F1904859372%2Fsr%3D8-10%2Fqid%3D1171853924%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">End Times: The Death of the Fourth Estate</a>, </i>a collection of essays on the media, many of which first appeared on <i>CounterPunch</i>. The two provide an important look at the U.S. political system, and especially the role of the Democrats, in <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDimes-Worth-Difference-Beyond-Counterpunch%2Fdp%2F1904859038%2Fsr%3D8-6%2Fqid%3D1171853924%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Dime's Worth of Difference: Beyond the Lesser of Two Evils</a> </i>and <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAl-Gore-Manual-Alexander-Cockburn%2Fdp%2F1859848036%2Fsr%3D8-1%2Fqid%3D1171853924%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Al Gore: A User's Manuel</a></i>.<p>
For a more general socialist analysis of the Democrats, you can download an ISO Web book by Lance Selfa, <i><a href="http://www.internationalsocialist.org/resources.html" target="_blank">The Democratic Party and the Politics of Lesser Evilism</a></i>.
</td></tr></table>
